## Dietary Alignment Trials

### Randomized Controlled Trials (RCTs)

[[!table  data="""
URL                                         | Author (Year)                | N (Ctrl/Exp) | Subject Selection  | Duration  | Diets Compared            | Most Interesting Outcome (causal proximity to QALYs, magnitude, p-value)
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34377527/> | Wahls et al (2021)           | 77 (39/38)   | Multiple Sclerosis | 24 weeks  | Wahls vs Swank            | Mental MSQoL +11.3 (p<0.0001) vs Swank (ns); Physical MSQoL +14.5. Fatigue reduced in both.
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/32213121/> | Lee et al (2021)             | 15 (4/6/5)   | Multiple Sclerosis | 12 weeks  | Wahls vs keto vs usual    | Wahls: significant within-group MFIS fatigue reduction (p=0.02), maintained cognition
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/30050374/> | Irish et al (2017)           | 17 (9/8)     | Multiple Sclerosis | 3 months  | Wahls vs usual diet       | FSS -1.6 (p=0.03); MSQOL-mental +17.7% (p=0.02); MSQOL-physical improved (p=0.03); dominant 9-HPT -12.1% (p=0.02)
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/27235022/> | Otten et al (2017)           | 32 (16/16)   | Type 2 Diabetes    | 12 weeks  | Paleo +/- Exercise        | Fat mass -5.7 kg (PD) / -6.7 kg (PD+Ex), both p<0.001; HbA1c -0.9% (p<0.001); HOMA-IR -45%.
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/27216013/> | Fontes-Villalba et al (2016) | 13 crossover | Type 2 Diabetes    | 2x3 mo    | Paleo vs Diabetes         | Fasting leptin decreased more with Paleo (Cohen's d=-1.26, p=0.023).
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/25828624/> | Masharani et al (2015)       | 24 (10/14)   | Type 2 Diabetes    | 14 days   | Paleo vs ADA              | Insulin sensitivity improved in most resistant subjects (r=0.40, p=0.02); glucose/lipids improved.
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/23890471/> | Jonsson et al (2013)         | 13 crossover | Type 2 Diabetes    | 2x3 mo    | Paleo vs Diabetes         | Paleo more satiating per calorie (satiety quotient/energy p=0.004).
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/21118562/> | Jonsson et al (2010)         | 29 (15/14)   | Type 2 Diabetes    | 12 weeks  | Paleo vs Mediterranean    | Paleo more satiating per calorie (p=0.04 energy, p=0.03 satiety/cal); leptin -31% vs -18%.
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/19604407/> | Jonsson et al (2009)         | 13 crossover | Type 2 Diabetes    | 2x3 mo    | Paleo vs Diabetes         | HbA1c -0.4% (p=0.01), TG -0.4 mmol/L (p=0.003), weight -3 kg (p=0.01), HDL +0.08 (p=0.03).
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/17583796/> | Lindeberg et al (2007)       | 29 15/14     | Ischemic Heart     | 12 weeks  | Paleo vs Mediterranean    | AUC glucose decreased 26% Paleo vs 7% Med (p=0.001), independent of waist change (p=0.0008).
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/25304296/> | Boers et al (2014)           | 32 (14/18)   | Metabolic Syndrome | 2 weeks   | Paleo vs Dutch guidelines | SBP -9.1 mmHg (p=0.015), TG -0.89 mmol/L (p=0.001), HDL +0.15 (p=0.013), MetS features -1.07 (p=0.010).
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/26003334/> | Pastore et al (2015)         | 20 (?/?)     | Hypercholesterol   | 4 mo each | Paleo vs AHA              | TC, LDL, TG all decreased (p<0.001); HDL increased (p<0.001); independent of weight change.
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/28440046/> | Blomquist et al (2017)       | 70 (?/?)     | Obese              | 24 mo     | Paleo vs Prudent          | Android fat decreased more in PD (p=0.009 at 6mo); hs-CRP decreased (p=0.001 at 24mo).
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/26786351/> | Otten et al (2016)           | 70 (?/?)     | Obese              | 24 mo     | Paleo vs Low-Fat          | Liver fat -64% PD vs -43% LFD at 6mo (p<0.01); persistent -50% each at 24mo.
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/24473459/> | Mellberg et al (2014)        | 70 (?/?)     | Obese              | 24 mo     | Paleo vs NNR              | Fat mass -6.5 vs -2.6 kg at 6mo (p<0.001); TG lower in PD (p<0.001 at 6mo, p=0.004 at 24mo).
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/27223304/> | Genoni et al (2016)          | 39 (17/22)   | Overweight         | 4 weeks   | Paleo vs AGHE             | Weight loss -1.99 kg more in Paleo (p<0.001); no metabolic marker differences.
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/33844651/> | Fitzgerald et al (2021)      | 43 (?/?)     | General            | 8 weeks   | Diet+lifestyle vs None    | Horvath DNAmAge decreased 3.23 years vs controls (p=0.018); TG -25% (p=0.009).
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/25661189/> | Bligh et al (2015)           | ? crossover  | General            | 180 min   | Paleo meals vs WHO Ref    | GLP-1 and PYY increased (p=0.001, p<0.001); increased satiety.
